Step 9: Limitations (p. 28)
Marco receives ten points that must be spent on limitations. 
After some reading he chooses the following:
• Noticeable weakness: Women (Beautiful women): 2 points.
The protagonist likes women, is drawn to them and spellbound
by them, especially beautiful women. This is a sure source
of trouble.
• Tangible fear: Thick fog/smoke/gas: 3 points
• Nightmares: 2 points
The fear and nightmares stem from the war, Marco
decides that when the protagonist finds himself in a situation 
where visibility is severely limited by fog, smoke or
gas clouds he risks the fear taking over—a side effect
from the countless gas attacks at the front. The nightmares
the protagonist has are about the horrors he has seen
and experienced on the battlefields.
• Indebted (Completely): 2 points
Indebtedness means that the protagonist is in debt to
a person, a company or an organization. The debt doesn't
need to be further defined at this stage. However, it
is a good hook to build personal stories on.
• Basic code of honor
Not harm women or children: 1 point
The protagonist has a basic moral compass, a personal 
goal to never harm women or children. With
this the ten points have been used.
