**Intuitive [4]**
The person can put themselves in other people's situations,
analyze them from their perspective, and can draw
conclusions so real that they appear lifelike in the per-
son's mind.

**Requirements:** Empathy 7+
**Rule:** The person finds it easy to subconsciously sense
things about other people and can put themselves in others' situa-
tions in an eerily effective way. This understanding is often
very intense and fraught with anxiety. By reading criminal
records, psychological evaluations, police reports, and inter-
view summaries, the person can form a picture of another
person's habits, likely behaviors, underlying drives,
and motives. When an intuitive person who has studied a
case thoroughly visits a crime scene or communicates
with a suspect, the person may receive inner fragmentary im-
ages of events that have occurred. These images often appear
very frightening and tangible.

To receive such images requires the person to succeed with
a difficulty roll (Empathy), with a penalty (−5). If the
roll succeeds, the person receives a bonus (+2) in all forms of communi-
cation with a chosen individual whom the person knows through
study. This bonus applies primarily to dice rolls (Empathy)
but also to other forms of communication. The person may
also use the bonus for dice rolls (Resist) in situa-
tions where the chosen individual is present. The bonus is
also applied to dice rolls (Deduction) related to a
case in which the person is well-versed.

